Both of this week's two Deals of the Week were played last week at the ACBL Regional tournament in Palm Springs, California. The declarers on both of these deals are names that you will be familiar with. ^*BBill Gates^*N played this week's first deal and ^*BWarren Buffett^*N played this week's second deal (which will be presented at the end of the first deal). 

Bill and Warren are well known as two of the most successful and admired businessmen in history, but did you know that they are both fine bridge players as well? If you did not know this already, then you have probably not been reading the newspapers or watching TV very much during the last couple of years. Bill and Warren's interest in bridge has generated a great deal of positive (and badly needed) publicity for our game. It seems that the media is interested in anything that Bill and Warren find interesting. We are very fortunate that bridge is one of the primary sources of recreation for two of the most famous and well-respected people in the world.

Warren has enjoyed playing bridge for many years and "solid" is the best word we can think of to describe Warren's game. Warren is technically very proficient -  it is very rare to seem him make a serious card play mistake. Warren's greatest strengths as a bridge player, however, are his judgment and table presence. He seems to have a sixth sense that tells him what to lead, when to double, and how high to compete. Warren has played most of his bridge in a social setting, but he is more than capable of holding his own in the tournament world.
|
