nt||va|5|at|Bill is relatively new to the game of bridge. Bill's schedule prevents him from playing in a lot of tournaments, but he has studied the game intensely over the last couple of years and improved his skills at a dramatic pace as a result. Bill is what we would call a "creative" bridge player - he likes to try the occasional offbeat action in the bidding so that he can take note of its effect, thereby building up his pool of experience. Bill is also one of the only bridge players that we know (at any level) who is capable of performing advanced probability computations quickly and accurately at the table. It should come as no surprise to you that Bill Gates is ^*Bvery^*N good at math!

Bill and Warren spent 2 days at the Palm Springs Regional playing on a team with  ^*BSharon Osberg^*N, ^*BBridge Base Inc.^*N President ^*BFred Gitelman^*N, and Vice President ^*BSheri Winestock^*N. Sharon, a two time World Champion, is one of only a handful of women in North America who is capable of (and chooses to) compete at the highest level in open events. Sharon has been a close friend of both Warren and Bill for many years (and a good friend to Fred and Sheri as well). Sharon has also been the primary bridge mentor for both Warren and Bill and she has contributed greatly to both their skills and their enjoyment of the game. This team performed quite well in Palm Springs, finishing 4th and 5th in two Swiss Teams events in large fields that included several of the top players in North America.

What is it like playing bridge and hanging out with Bill Gates and Warren Buffett? It is a real treat! The bridge is always stimulating, as is the discussion of the hands after the session. With the kinds of minds that Warren and Bill have been blessed with, no bridge topic is too advanced to bring up. Besides the bridge, it is wonderful just to be around these guys. They are both brilliant, of course, but they are also both very humorous, knowledgeable and genuinely nice people. All bridge players are lucky that Bill and Warren love our game so much, but Fred and Sheri feel especially privileged to be able to call such great men their friends.

